The paper deals with the problem of online sequence prediction, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning a good set of experts using a training set of previously observed sequences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in the context of the problem, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
